-- Babcock & Wilcox Appoints Westinghouse’s Ferland to CEO
-- B y   J i m   P o l s o n
-- 2012-04-04T13:11:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-04/ferland-to-join-babcock-wilcox-from-westinghouse-correct-.html
Babcock & Wilcox Co. (BWC) , the power-
plant builder and defense contractor, appointed former
Westinghouse Electric Co. Chief Executive Officer Jim Ferland as
president and CEO, succeeding Brandon Bethards, who is retiring
April 19.  Ferland, 45, previously served as president of the Americas
division at Westinghouse Electric Corp., according to a
statement today from  Charlotte , North Carolina-based Babcock &
Wilcox. Westinghouse, the nuclear-reactor designer and
subsidiary of  Toshiba Corp. (6502) , announced yesterday the resignation
of Ferland, who had taken over as CEO of the unit April 1.  Bethards, 64, will resign from Babcock & Wilcox’s board of
directors May 8 and remain a consultant to the company for a
year, the company said. Bethards worked in the industry for 42
years, primarily at Babcock and Wilcox, according to the
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
